5: There are no monsters here either...
8:
That's weird. Shouldn't the
Kaleidoscope be swarming with them?
10:
Normally, I would be glad for the quiet,
but this stillness is unnatural...
11:
And there are tales of something
lurking deep in this labyrinth.
17:
What's this power I sense?
No... The dark arts!
21:
...Darkness residing in all creation. The
mysterious eyelids that veil the abyss.
23: Unfurl now, and reveal the truth!
28:
Well, that didn't go so well.
Another expected failure.
36:
Fight first, questions later!
They're going to attack him!
39:
Stay back. I am perfectly capable of
dealing with my own messes.
42:
Take form and defeat my foes—
Gladius!
46:
Sorry if I startled you. My name is
Liam Ilde. I'm a mage.
47:
It seems I owe you an explanation.
Do you have a few moments to spare?
53: And, you there. The floating one.
59:
I'd very much like to discuss the magic
that has been cast upon you.
69: So all of that was an experiment?
72:
For a scholar of the dark arts, this
labyrinth is brimming with mysteries—
more than could be covered in
a single lifetime.
74:
I've been trying to find its power source,
but as you know, my research can
prove... disastrous. I'll try to be more
careful next time.
80:
Or you could stop tampering with the
dark arts entirely.
81: Power like that can kill you.
86:
All power—whether it be of fire, water,
wind, thunder, or light—can kill you.
Though many people seem to
forget that.
87:
Now, it IS true that the dark arts are
poorly understood. In that sense, they
are quite dangerous to pursue.
88:
However, I won't abandon my research
now, not after leaving my home behind.
I understand my actions, thank you
very much.
93:
No matter what world you're in,
it seems mages never change...
98:
Ahem. But as I mentioned before,
I will try to be more careful next time.
99:
I think I'll start conducting research
in the depths of the Kaleidoscope,
where there is less risk of
collateral damage.
105:
You want to go into the depths?
On your own? That's pretty reckless.
109:
It's the most obvious way of
minimizing causalities.
118: Liam. Why not join us instead?
123: Excellent idea. I would love to.
129: Whoa! You sure decided that quick!
131:
Well, having other people around
reduces MY chances of dying. And I'm
sure YOU'D appreciate a new ally and
a way to keep an eye on me.
135:
You are also able to study the curse
the Lord of Shadow has cast upon me.
137:
Heh. See? It's a win-win situation.
Only logical to proceed together.
141: Sigh... That's one way of looking at it.
144:
Well then, shall we be off? Time wasted
is time that could be spent studying
this place.
149:
Did you really want to keep an eye
on him?
152:
I do not believe he is evil. But he is too
confident in his own power.
153:
I worry about what will happen if he is
left alone.
157:
But I believe you two will be a good
influence.
